news.title: Land for condo not fully given, HC allows Ace Infracity eight year 'zero period' waiver
news.para: It was in 2014 that a consortium led by Lotus Green Constructions Pvt Ltd was allotted 12 lakh sqm in Sector 150 to develop Sports City. Of the total land, Ace was supposed to get 60,000sqm for developing residential projects.

news.title: Haryana RERA's benches yet to appoint a chairman
news.para: In the absence of adequate authorities, writ petitions filed before both the benches of H-Rera are piling up, giving an undue advantage to builders and developers.

news.title: DLF buys office space in Gurugram for Rs 81 crore
news.para: The building is the costliest office space tower in Gurgaon. The space was owned by Madhur Maini and has been leased to WeWork India.

news.title: Bank of Spain Governor sees no need to extend mortgage support
news.para: Last week, Spain's Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez said the new coalition government was planning to extend the annual income threshold to qualify for mortgage relief support to $41,283 as part of a set of measures to help families cope with higher borrowing costs.

news.title: SBB offer fails to address creditor obligations: Fir Tree Partners
news.para: Loss-making SBB, which is at the centre of a wider Swedish property crash, said on Thursday it would offer to buy back hybrid and senior securities for up to $650 million as the group looks to cut debt on its balance sheet.

news.title: China: Seazen Holdings to raise $280 million via onshore bonds-term sheet
news.para: The three-year notes are expected to have a coupon of 3.5%-4.5% and will be guaranteed by state-owned China Bond Insurance Corp, the term sheet showed.

news.title: Bihar government asks district authorities to curb illegal sand mining
news.para: The process for setting up such a surveillance infrastructure has already been initiated in Bhojpur, Jamui, Nawada, Rohtas, Aurangabad and Kaimur districts.

news.title: Sunac China Holdings says restructuring conditions satisfied
news.para: In early October, a Hong Kong court approved Sunac China Holdings' about $9 billion offshore restructuring proposal that is expected to be a template for cash-strapped peers in a key sector battered since mid-2021.

news.title: Kanpur: PMAY beneficiaries receive keys of houses
news.para: MPs Satya Deo Pachouri and Devendra Singh Bhole, mayor Pramila Pandey, Saroj Kureel, Neelima Katiyar, joint secretary environment forest and climate change Satyajit Mishra, chief development officer Sudhir Kumar and other officials were present in the fucntion.

news.title: Pune: Builder, finance firm manager booked on charge of duping homebuyer of Rs 16 lakh
news.para: The third suspect is the homebuyer’s friend. He had introduced the victim to the builder, sub-inspector Vaibhav Patil of the Dehu Road police said.

news.title: Hanto Workspaces raises Rs 15 crore in seed funding led by KredX founder
news.para: Hanto aims to expand its operations to other metros and tier 2 cities like Hyderabad, Pune across the country over the next 5 years with a revenue target of over Rs 700 crore by 2028.

news.title: Trichy: Applications invited for building plan approvals
news.para: In a statement, Trichy collector M Pradeepkumar said that the Tamil Nadu government has introduced an online service to apply for plan approval for residential and commercial buildings, residential plots and industries in rural areas.

news.title: Poor response to Chandigarh housing board auctions
news.para: Nearly a year ago, CHB had offered on auction its 92 commercial properties. Of these, it again offered 88 commercial properties last month, but failed to find any takers.

news.title: Bengaluru: 15 lakh properties without khata under scanner
news.para: BBMP chief commissioner Tushar Giri Nath said the city has more than 20 lakh ‘A’ khata and 7 lakh ‘B’ khata properties. Many owners allegedly do not opt for ‘B’ khata’ to avoid property tax payment.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh CM directs officials to settle pending cases of mutation by Jan 20
news.para: The high-power committee under the chairmanship of the CM reviewed the pending revenue cases in the state and asked all the deputy commissioners to dispose of the pending cases on mission mode.

news.title: Odisha CM inaugurates three housing complexes for slum dwellers in Bhubaneswar
news.para: The three housing complexes inaugurated by Patnaik were: Keshari Residency built in Satya Nagar, Buddha Vihar in Chandrasekharpur and Barunei Enclave in Subudhipur.

news.title: Gurugram: 16 building sites fined Rs 7 lakh for GRAP violations, owners served notices
news.para: On behalf of the deputy commissioner, district town planner (planning) and three district town planners (enforcement) have been appointed as duty magistrates to tackle violations of GRAP rules.

news.title: Bengaluru: 26 buildings in layout face BBMP action over building plan violations
news.para: As part of its crackdown, BBMP identified 70 buildings in the layout and demanded that the owners submit their approved plans. Of the 30 plans received, 26 were found to be in violation, encompassing unauthorised additional floors and failure to adhere to setbacks.

news.title: Wipro to sell office assets in Hyderabad, Bengaluru
news.para: The country's fourth-largest IT firm recently implemented a compulsory hybrid work policy requiring employees to report to work from the office at least three days a week.

news.title: Gurugram: 96 cases filed, 29 held for illegal construction in four months
news.para: Police said on Monday that the cases were registered after the Enforcement Bureau police station was set up in Gurgaon.
